ey saved the same amount each year on your birthday and earned 8% per year on their investments.","marks":[]}],"data":{}},{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"a","startValue":1},"ref":"056c25d0-2a96-484e-90b5-4b4fe879ac70","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"afa225e1-6099-4e5c-accb-c915301b3a3b","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"3d250bcb-574d-47b3-93c7-87643ed63d67","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"How much would they have to save each year to reach their goal?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"2eb419c6-f621-42ab-8804-0429633f7f76","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"ad8b496b-c994-42b2-9aba-2b0943c41f25","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"If they think you will take five years instead of four to graduate and decide to have $200,000 saved just in case, how much more would they have to save each year to reach their new goal?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]}]}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"41b08106-e3df-4c11-a717-0e0e57c1ce9c"}]}]},{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-image","config":{"url":"urn:aero:4ab45a10-44e0-11ed-bcef-d5307f42495c","alt":"","caption":"","layout":{"captionPosition":"Below"},"credit":"","activityLabel":"","activityTitle":""},"height":37,"ref":"56a75547-7453-43a4-9a43-830f624e1006"}]}]},{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"1","startValue":21},"ref":"9a8c4de8-d0e8-4525-8e72-cb1ac4395bdb","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"befc3452-74a1-4bfe-89c8-4b00cb46042a","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"afa318c3-bac0-4859-8217-b1198b62553e","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"When you purchased your car, you took out a five-year annual-payment loan with an interest rate of 6% per year. The annual payment on the car is $5000. You have just made a payment and have now decided to pay off the loan by repaying the outstanding balance. What is the payoff amount for the following scenarios?","marks":[]}],"data":{}},{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"a","startValue":1},"ref":"f0eeb90c-2f8d-4801-81ce-a0239949ce72","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"196352b2-164f-42be-819e-2218257ae04d","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"a2801946-2d94-4f2a-87bd-ec81a87f1dfb","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"You have owned the car for one year (so there are four years left on the loan)?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"8b40cd54-40e9-41c8-87d4-0aa14e1e33d4","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"f5bcb405-83bc-41d5-852b-adc849d7cd6f","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"You have owned the car for four years (so there is one year left on the loan)?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"ad5b031f-aad9-4ccf-a544-f3d5d46fb575","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"01594ab7-8b6f-4f94-9e2f-65936c6cf4aa","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"You figure that the total cost of college will be $100,000 per year 18 years from today. If your discount rate is 8% compounded annually, what is the present value today of four years of college costs starting 18 years from today?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"bb3ba206-b5ef-4c09-a4d4-3b960908ea98"}]}]},{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-image","config":{"url":"urn:aero:4ab45a10-44e0-11ed-bcef-d5307f42495c","alt":"","caption":"","layout":{"captionPosition":"Below"},"credit":"","activityLabel":"","activityTitle":""},"height":37,"ref":"2012adfc-c848-4885-aeb4-411e5734c2ec"}]}]},{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"1","startValue":23},"ref":"188d4118-cf48-461e-92c7-f40d5ade078d","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"0d6231ca-d8de-4e5c-8d20-f0c67136a69b","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"c5545d20-de33-4048-9e55-055988d7f888","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Assume that Social Security promises you $40,000 per year starting when you retire 45 years from today (the first $40,000 will be paid 45 years from now). If your discount rate is 7%, compounded annually, and you plan to live for 15 years after retiring (so that you will receive a total of 16 payments including the first one), what is the value today of Social Security’s promise?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"475c3359-a71f-403b-9716-eb34a8c4c263","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"40444eb7-b3d0-491a-9a39-1e157b4fcf07","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"When Alex Rodriguez moved to the Texas Rangers in 2001, he received a lot of attention for his “$252 million” contract (the total of the payments promised was $252 million). He later moved to the Yankees, but assume the following in order to determine the value of his contract when he signed it:","marks":[]}],"data":{}},{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"90a1bccd-0b8c-4390-9b57-08adc4ba3c64","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Rodriguez earns $16 million in the first year, $17 million in years 2 through 4, $19 million in years 5 and 6, $23 million in year 7, and $27 million in years 8 through 10. He also receives his $10 million signing bonus spread equally over the first 5 years ($2 million per year). His deferred payments begin in 2011. The deferred payment amounts total $33 million and are $5 million, then $4 million, then eight amounts of $3 million (ending in 2020). However, the actual payouts will be different. All of the deferred payments will earn 3% per year until they are paid. For example, the $5 million is deferred from 2001 to 2011, or 10 years, meaning that it will actually be $6.7196 million when paid. Assume that the $4 million payment deferred to 2012 is deferred from 2002 (each payment is deferred 10 years).","marks":[]}],"data":{}},{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"7d1c3177-daba-49ea-86d4-7c32e919598d","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"The contract is a 10-year contract, but each year has a deferred component so that cash flows are paid out over a total of 20 years. The contractual payments, signing bonus, and deferred components are given below. Note that, by contract, the deferred components are not paid in the year they are earned, but instead are paid (plus interest) 10 years later.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"a03a5b5c-b286-497c-bb20-ed234e368afc"}]}]},{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-table","config":{"activityLabel":"","instructions":"","tableCaptionText":"","activityTitle":"","tableTitle":"","captions":"","credit":""},"value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"data":{"id":"ch04intbl03"},"nodes":[{"data":{},"nodes":[{"data":{},"nodes":[{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"2001","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"object":"block","type":"table-data","ref":"cef72974-2c6d-475e-84bd-c4648c164a68"},{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"2002","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"object":"block","type":"table-data","ref":"e996ebec-2724-4870-8198-fca7c02192bb"},{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"2003","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"object":"block","type":"table-data","ref":"653226b9-87cd-46ed-8228-78157250